During the course the students get an overview on the etiology and mechanisms of development of basic syndromes and diseases at the level of organism, tissue, cell, and molecules as well as on the effects of pathogenic changes on the functions of organism.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide the students with the basic knowledge on pathophysiology, useful to understand the etiology and pathogenesis of diseases and to use this knowledge for diagnosis and treatment of diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who graduated the course: - knows pathologic processes and mechanisms of development; - knows ethiology of the disorders of water and salt balance, acid-base balance, carbohydratis  and lipoprotein metabolism with main compensatory mechanisms in this case;  - knows alterations in function and regulation of organs and systems during pathologic processes and diseases and can also analyse the mechanisms of pathogenesis.
